message.content:
To get to the grocery store that is 1km away in Mexico, you have a few options:

1. Walking: If the weather is pleasant and you enjoy walking, you can simply walk to the grocery store. It will take you approximately 10-15 minutes to cover a distance of 1km.

2. Cycling: If you have a bicycle or can rent one, cycling can be a convenient and quick way to reach the grocery store. It will take you around 5-7 minutes to cover the 1km distance.

3. Public transportation: Depending on the availability of public transportation in your area, you can check for buses or minibusses that pass by or near the grocery store. You can ask locals or check online for the nearest bus stop and the route that will take you there.

4. Taxi or rideshare: If you prefer a more comfortable and direct option, you can take a taxi or use a ridesharing service like Uber or Didi. These services are widely available in Mexico and can take you directly to the grocery store.

Remember to consider factors such as cost, convenience, and personal preference when choosing the mode of transportation.
